. Dissonance, conflict, tensions are inevitable ingredients in our development toward self-actualization as we struggle with the sticky matter of life. The challenges are many, the roads are arduous, and the journey is lengthy but who cannot say immensely worthwhile and "Value-able".  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMoral education. 0aÉducation morale. 4aEducation. 4aLanguage Arts & Disciplines. 7aEDUCATION / Testing & Measurement.2bisacsh1 aAlexander, Robert E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeck, Clive, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColby, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDamon, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDebrock, Guy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGibbs, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHersh, Richard H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKohlberg, Lawrence, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLitke, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeyer, John R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeyer, John R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMorgenson, Donald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPaolitto, Diana Pritchard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPuka, Bill, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpeicher-Dubin, Betsy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTurner, Francis J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe